{{Infobox person |name=Joyce Eliason |birth_date={{birth date and age|1934|5|14}} |birth_place=[[United States]] |occupation=[[Screenwriter]], [[television producer]] }}
'''Joyce Eliason''' (born May 14, 1934) is an American television writer and producer. She is best known for writing TV miniseries including ''Titanic'' and ''The Last Don'', and for the TV film ''The Jacksons: An American Dream''.<ref>[http://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/joyce_eliason/ Joyce Eliason at Rotton Tomatoes]</ref> Eliason was one of the writers for the hit television series ''Love, American Style''<ref>{{IMDb title|id=0063925|title=Love, American Style}}</ref> and wrote her first screenplay ''Tell Me a Riddle'' in 1980.<ref>{{IMDb title|id=0081611|title=Tell Me a Riddle}}</ref><ref>[http://www.tnt.tv/movies/movietitle/?oid=26836 Movies on TNT: ''A Perfect Day'']</ref>
Eliason wrote two books before becoming a screenwriter, ''Fresh Meat/Warm Weather'' in 1974 and ''Laid Out'' in 1976.<ref>Eliason, Joyce, Fresh Meat/Warm Weather, Harper & Row, 1974, {{ISBN|0-06-011241-7}}</ref><ref>Eliason, Joyce, Laid Out, Harper & Row, 1976, {{ISBN|0-06-011119-4}}</ref>
==Selected filmography== Eliason is principally a writer, but she also frequently serves as a producer on films which she has written. A partial filmography is shown below.<ref>[https://movies.nytimes.com/person/168085/Joyce-Eliason The New York Times: Joyce Eliason filmography]</ref><ref>[http://www.filmreference.com/film/28/Joyce-Eliason.html film reference: Joyce Eliason Biography]</ref>
